Take Home for Thrive


Structure

/src
    Contains the code files. 

    challenge.rb is the main starting point
    user.rb and company.rb are classes used to store the output_top_ups_data
    verification.rb is used to verify the data for a given user or company json

/spec

    Contains the unit tests. The unit tests are written in rspec. 
    They also can be used for used for documentation


To run the program

    `ruby src/challenge.rb` in the command line from the root directory. This will output the results in the terminal and to a file named "output.txt"

